The paper focuses on designing clustering algorithms for processing large datasets in MapReduce, which is a distributed computing framework. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical analysis of the algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Mining (cs.DM).
